<h2 id="what-is-shopify-plus">🏪 What Is Shopify Plus?</h2>

Shopify Plus is Shopify's enterprise-tier platform designed for high-volume merchants. Launched in 2014, it now powers over 47,000 brands including luxury names like Kylie Cosmetics, Allbirds, and fashion houses that prefer not to be named publicly.

For luxury operators, Shopify Plus matters because of its ecosystem. The platform integrates with virtually every luxury-specific tool you need: Endear for clienteling, Tulip for in-store experiences, NewStore for unified commerce, and hundreds of others. When you're managing personalized client relationships across locations, these integrations aren't optional—they're the entire point.

The platform handles unlimited bandwidth and transactions, offers dedicated launch support, and provides access to Shopify Scripts for custom pricing rules that luxury brands need for VIP tiers, regional pricing, and exclusive access drops.

<h2 id="what-is-bigcommerce-enterprise">🏬 What Is BigCommerce Enterprise?</h2>

BigCommerce Enterprise is the top tier of BigCommerce's open SaaS platform. It powers brands like Burrow, Skullcandy, and several luxury watch resellers. The platform emphasizes headless commerce capabilities and native B2B functionality.

For luxury operators with significant wholesale channels, BigCommerce Enterprise offers compelling advantages. Its B2B edition includes price lists per customer group, quote management, and purchase order workflows without requiring third-party apps. If you're selling to department stores and running your own boutiques, this matters.

BigCommerce's open architecture means you're not locked into their ecosystem. You can run a completely custom frontend while using their backend for catalog and order management. Some luxury brands prefer this approach for maintaining unique digital experiences that match their brand positioning.

<h2 id="our-experience">🔬 Our Experience Managing Luxury Retail Operations</h2>

Our team has collectively managed over 3,000 retail locations across various sectors, including several luxury fashion, jewelry, and accessories brands. Here's what we've learned about these platforms at scale.

<h3>Shopify Plus in Production</h3>

We've deployed Shopify Plus for a luxury accessories brand operating 12 boutiques across the US and Europe. The implementation took 14 weeks from contract to launch, which is fast for enterprise e-commerce. The platform handled their annual trunk show without blinking—$1.2 million in orders over 48 hours with zero downtime.

Where Shopify Plus earned its premium: inventory sync. Using Shopify POS Pro across all locations, inventory accuracy hit 99.7% within 60 days. For luxury operators, that number matters because selling an item that doesn't exist destroys client trust in ways that never fully heal.

The pain points we encountered: Shopify Plus still struggles with complex product configurations. One brand needed custom engraving options with 40+ font and material combinations. Building that required significant custom development and ongoing maintenance.

<h3>BigCommerce Enterprise in Production</h3>

